{"id":"project-LICHEN-rjfl","title":"vectors.rs hex_to_array panics on incorrect length input","description":"File: rust/lichen-oscore/tests/vectors.rs
Lines: 91-96

The hex_to_array function panics if the hex string doesn't decode to exactly N bytes:
```rust
fn hex_to_array<const N: usize>(hex: &str) -> [u8; N] {
    let bytes = hex_to_bytes(hex);
    let mut arr = [0u8; N];
    arr.copy_from_slice(&bytes);  // PANICS if bytes.len() != N
    arr
}
```

If a test vector in oscore.json has incorrect length for master_secret (needs 16 bytes), the test will panic with an unhelpful 'slice length mismatch' error.

Impact: Poor error messages when test vectors are malformed. Test-only code, so low priority.

Fix: Either validate length and return Result, or use try_into() with better error message:
```rust
fn hex_to_array<const N: usize>(hex: &str) -> [u8; N] {
    let bytes = hex_to_bytes(hex);
    bytes.try_into().expect(&format!(
        "hex_to_array: expected {} bytes, got {}",
        N, bytes.len()
    ))
}
